,Recommended,263300,16562287,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,Tyknu,"I absolutely love BlazBlue, and the game itself is very fun, so I'm giving this a positive score, but there are a few things that you should know before buying this game. First off, this version of the game does not have online play. This is also a game that you will want to have a controller to play, preferably two of them in case you want to play with a friend when you have them over. Finally,the last thing that new players should know is that the release of Blazblue Continuum Shift Extend makes this game obsolete due to the fact that it covers the storyline from both this game and the sequel while adding new characters."
