,Recommended,263300,9134107,"Posted: 15 February, 2014",all,王子,"Should you buy BlazBlue Calamity Trigger on steam?MaybeI love the blazblue franchise and spent many hours with cs2, the game was a blast to play and as a result the moment I saw this hit steam I instant purchased it. However Just like GG isuka I got burned with a terrible port, no online play, lack of controller support for anything that isn't a 360 controller (it took me several hours of finicky work arounds just so I could use my logitech usb controller)  and a mass amount of confusion on why we got the insanely old version of this series.Due to GFWL shutting down (which this game was original for) it seems the developer just ported the game over to steam to make some more money off the title and instead of adding in a new netcode for online play they just stripped the feature completly. It is unknown at this time if purchasing this game will have any impact on whether or not future titles will come to pc and steam. One can hope But I will not being holding my breath.For 10 dollars you will get however a great story mode with fun loveable characters and the ability to play around with imo one of the best fighting systems out there. The game is fantastic and if it had some form of online play I would start gifting copies of this game, to my far away friends that is how much fun it is. You also get the soundtrack which is fantastic on its own and for the price it might even be worth it to you.I will recommend this game as for me I would have probably still purchased it knowning it didn't have online play attached, however for many of you this will be a deal breaker, and I would not recommend this game to you."
