76561198123093628,Recommended,263300,33099961,Posted: 1 July,all,doggo,"Get it on sale if you're interested at all in the BB universe and story; it will help you understand what is going on in the later games. I would not recommend this game if you are mainly interested in versus modes.Pros:- visual novel-like story with lots of endings and decisions to make- every character is unique and has their own playstyle- the visuals of the game still hold up pretty well- english dub that is actually enjoyable and gives the characters a lot of personality- local multiplayer- really good soundtrack with fitting tracks for each characterCons:- no online multiplayer (without mods)- very limited character selection by today's standards (12 characters)- no tutorial mode as in newer BB titles, and no stylish type- getting 100% story completion means a lot of backtracking and purposefully letting CPU'skill you so you can see the gameover cutscene- slight framerate issues (might just be on my end, but I can run the newer games perfectly fine)- combat feels a bit slower than the newer titlesOverall I think it's a good game, but it's definitely not as polished as the newer entries in the series."
,Recommended,263300,18181628,"Posted: 24 September, 2015",all,RetriButioN,"If you're a fan of fighting games, you should definitely play BlazBlue series. BlazBlue is a fine series with a complicated story. Story itself is mainly told through images and voiced text, there are no 3D cutscenes or anime-style movies. The main Gameplay is very complicated and takes a long time to master, however BlazBlue Calamity Trigger is a Single-Player Only title. If you're looking for competitive multiplayer, you should buy Continuum Shift version.I'd highly recommend Calamity Trigger to all Fighting Games fans simply because of the amazing story and intriguing gameplay. Soundtrack is one of the best too and you would be getting it for free, what a bargain!"
