,Recommended,263300,28675612,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,DRUNK_CANADIAN,"BlazBlue: Calamity Trigger, a solid 2d fighter with a easy to learn, difficult to master combat system.  The gameplay itself is standard acceptable fighter fair, which is relatively accessible, the 4 button setup for different movesets and the relative easy of blocking and initiating combos allow you to jump in....however chaining and more complex setups take a long while to master. The fighting all the same is rewarding. The real reason you should play this game however isn't the fighting mechanics or the unique feel of the fighters (different unique playstyles) but rather for the story and personalities of the cast. The game does an excellent job in its storytelling having branching ""choose your own ending"" style gameplay for each of the characters, and locking the true ending...which is ultimately based on the sum of the individual stories behind completing the game as each character. By the time you finally get to game's end you will have a good understanding of the BlazBlue universe and have enjoyed multiple conclusions which are oddly canon (play the game....you will get it). So in summary, as far as stories go, for a fighting game, BlazBlue has arguably the best, and as the first installment, I fully recommend playing this game before moving on to others in the series. That being said this game does have some optimization bugs so be warned in that respect."
