76561198041943500,Recommended,263300,9127676,"Posted: 15 February, 2014",all,Holmborn,"Blazblue: Calamity Trigger is the first in the trilogy, and it shows.For a proper review of Calamity TRigger, id recomend reading a different review than this one, as i will only be talking about the PC Port.For a PC Port, Calamity Trigger does a decent job. They include some key features, such as a good amount of Resolution options, Anti Aliasing, Bloom and sound options. Its a sprite based fighting game, so there isnt really that much to change when it comes to the visual options.The framerate is quite off though. My PC is not exactly top tier, but its definetly not low tier either. Mid tier, ive gotten drops to 45FPS which is really bad in a fighting game. Other than that, the game usually runs at a solid 60FPS.The game also doesnt handle Alt+Tabbing out of the game that well, as ive seen the sprites bugging out by doing so. This can range from completely dissapearing  or the colours being completely off.There is no online, though i personally dont feel this matters. Calamity Trigger is an old game, and the balance is VERY off. Multiple characters has 1 hit kill combos/setups, so going online you probably wouldnt be having that much of a good time.The game does allow for Local 1v1, so if you want to play with friends, there is that option.The Story is good. Its done in a Visual Novel style, and should take about 10-20 hours to go through, depending on how much of a completionist you are.It does have ""Supposed to lose"" fights, so in a few fights you actually fail when you win. The game also has some fights which require a ""Distortion Finish"" which is basically requires you to win with a Super move. Both of these got changed in the later installments of the series, except for a select few matches where distortion/Astral finish was required.Id say, if you buy this game, dont buy it for a Fighting Game solely. Buy it if you are interrested in the story of Blazblue and possibly want to see the rest of the games ported to PC. As a fan of the series, id say its worth it. You also get the soundtrack which is amazing. Its a mix between Instrumental Rock and Vocal remixed versions of the instrumental songs(Lyrics are in Japanese)."
