,Recommended,263300,9122900,"Posted: 15 February, 2014",all,FAQ,"As a person who grew up with playing Neo Geo's King of Fighter I can say that I did enjoy playing this game. Something that BlazBlue lacks is a large selection of characters (there are 12 in total). Though, because of that, every single character has their own unique fighting style and personality. The pace of this game is just right and the characters are somewhat balanced once you get a grip of their combos/attacks. BlazBlue's soundtracks are also great, more than that; they're included when you buy this game!This game features a story mode which requires you to play through all character's story to unlock more content. It's basically a visual novel. With that said, there are different paths you can take which leads to different endings.Surprisingly the story of this game was quite deep (complex?) and far more what I've expected. It was quite entertaining and it did add a lot more value to the game. The voice acting for some characters however (like Ragna) was terrible, while others (Rachel) was really good.And of course, there is an arcade mode as well!If you're new to this genre, watch a gameplay of this game. That's probably the best way to find out if this is a game for you (there are no gameplay videos in the store page).I personally don't really care about online mode, thus I did not take it inconsideration when I made this into one of my recommended games. As of now, there is no online mode."
