,Not Recommended,263300,11002133,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,Smallcrits,"Let's face it. This game is an outdated, badly ported, mess of a title. After following the examples of how to make this game run decently, I would still suggest that it isn't worth $10 on Steam. Buy it on console if you are interested. It will actually work and probably cost less.Once the game is downloaded, it locks you into around 30fps. If you are even a mediocre fighting game player, you will know that that is a dealbreaker. There are also the lag spikes you would normally see from a bad console to PC port that is all too common on steam. The second deal breaker is that this title is very outdated in format. There is a reason developers put out new, updated titles in a franchise like fixing the engine, not just to make money. An outdated format brings me to the last deal breaker, there is no online. Some of us, me included, bought Clamity trigger just to have a blazblue game to play since I do not own a console. No online isn't a fatal fault, but a fault nonetheless.I would also rather not suggest people buy the game just in hope of better ports and updated titles to the franchise. Why show support for Arc when they have shown how little effort they are willing to put into a port already? I would much prefer donating to a fundraising campaign with the incentive of a decent port so that there is some form of obligation to make a good product by the developers. I will not give a hollow smile and say ""Good effort out there! You will do better next time I'm sure."" What I hope is that this was just a prototype for Arc to practice on and that the next titles will be actually playable."
