,Recommended,263300,13033697,"Posted: 21 November, 2014",all,123GermanGamer,"This game is AWSOME!!!Disclaimer: This review is going to be long,so please only read this if you have enough time on you hands. Thank you and have fun.I've played the original BlazBlue on Xbox (Arcade) and I love it that they did a remake on that game (or more like a PC port). My expections were pretty high and I didn't get dissapointed!But first thing first:-> Spoiler warning for the story! If you haven't played the ""real ending"",skip to the next arrow!-The Story:There isn't really much of a story... it's a tournament fighter like Street Fighter,what do you expect? Oh well,here's the Story: Ragna and his brother Jin were normal boys who lived in a church/an orphanage with nuns. One day the building started to burn and Ragna quickly noticed it (He was in the Woods BTW). As he retuned,Jin was standing there,telling him that he's the reason this happened. At first he didn't understand,but then it was too late. Jin cut off Ragna's arm. Now we're skipping ahead at least 10 years. Ragna's grown up and wants to get revenge for his arm and the nuns Jin had killed. On his way to Jin he met some people and most of em' wanted his ""Azure Grimoire"", wich is giving him Demon like powers. At the NOL HQ,the meets Jin to finally settle the score, but they were interrupted when a gate opened,that connected the ""Real World"" to the ""Under World"". There he met V-13,a robot like girl who says that she's his sister. In the final cutscene, Rachel Alucard uses a spell with wich she's trying to close the gate. Of course, it didn't work-> Spoiler free Arrow right here!And thats the whole story! Of course, it's incomplete. It's getting more complete in the 2nd game,Continuum Shift,wich will be soon available on Steam. Overall the story is Ok.-The Characters:This is an interessting thing to talk about. You have 11 playable characters. Those would be ""Ragna the Bloodedge"",""Bang Shishigami"",""Jin Kisaragi"",""Noel Vermillion"",""Carl Clover"",""Rachel Alurad"",""Taokaka"",""Litchi Faye-Ling"",""Arakune"",""V-13"" and ""Hakumen"",Each with differen attack speeds and Distortion Finishes. And that's really a shame. Don't get me wrong,I like the characters, but in what minds did they think to leave out Hazama??? He is one of,if THE, coolest characters in this entire game! But he's only an NPC... at least he's playable in Continuum Shift.-The Gamemodes:That's a simple one. There are only some modes. Story,Arcade and Online. There are the most important ones and the only ones.-The Gameplay:This game plays as you would expect it to. There's a light,medium and heavy attack button,Special attack buttons, Combos for Distortion Finishes (ect.). If you've ever played any fighting game like Street Fighter or Tekken,you know how to play BlazBlue!There's nothing more to say to this I guess... Moving on!-The Graphic:Oh my god, the graphic... It's so beautiful. All characters look like they belong in an Anime, the intro cutscene and some other cutscenes are drawn (Animestyle) and the backgrounds are not just ""there"", they feel alive because something's allways happening! If you're a fan of Anime,you're gonna like the visuals of this game,bright and shiny on one side, dark and kinda scary on the other. A perfect mix!-The Music:I've saved the best for last!https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n8pKHTS0nh8THIS says everything I need to say. The music a AWSOME! It's Powerfull,Epic and most importantly remindable. If I think about BlazBlue, the song that always comes to my mind would be Taokakas theme. It's so happy and *Derp* at the same time...It's perfect for Taokaka.All in all,this game ROCKS! You should DEFINATLY,DEFINATLY buy this game! C'mon! Buy it allready! Go ahead!My final Score for this game is 10/10 Points. It's simply a masterpiece.Heeeeey,you made it to the end! Thanks for reading my Review of BlazBlue: Calamity Trigger! Hope you liked it!!!"
