76561198019143176,Not Recommended,263300,10718597,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,Kensington,"Trying Too HardAs a big fan of the Guilty Gear franchise, and Persona 4: Arena, I had...somewhat high hopes for this game. I'd heard what I'd heard, and little of it good, but still...a 7.5 wasn't too much to ask, was it?This game is, in a nutshell, Guilty Gear if it was trying too hard. For someone who has played this, GG and P4A, it's so easy to see this as the middle child, with neither the love and care of the former, nor the time-tested wisdom of the latter.The character designs in this game are atrocious. Each character has been over-designed to the point of becoming completely generic and uninteresting, a feat which I'd've thought impossible. Ragna the Bloodedge, a main character with a name somehow stupider than Sol Badguy, looks like an anime character merged with a matryoshka doll. You could shuck ten layers off this character and still not get to the actual man beneath. Every anime trope is piled on these characters in order to make them memorable, and a similar concept has been followed with the game's combat.The Drive button is an interesting idea. I can see how it evolved into the P4A persona attacks. But here, it creates a combat system that is equal parts chaotic and clunky. I fully admit to scrub status; I am not particularly GOOD at Blazblue. But that is irrelevant here; I'm terrible at 3rd Strike, I'm terrible at P4A, I'm terrible at friggin Skullgirls; but it doesn't impact my enjoyment of the game.With only local co-op available, the AI's gotta stand up. And it just doesn't. Set it to highest difficulty, pick Officer Moe, and spam Down+D. Oh, look what happened. PERFECT.Is it? Is itreally?Main takeaway? People like to play fighting games for a lot of reasons, and the big two for me are the feel of the combat, and the design of the characters. And in both cases, Arcsys seems to have taken the approach of ""throw stuff at a wall and see what sticks.""What they didn't realize is that the wall was sticky. Very sticky.Forreasons.Lookin' at you, Faye-Ling."
