,Recommended,263300,16337729,"Posted: 12 June, 2015",all,the_aY,"I originally purchased this game on PS3, and had a fun time with it.There are a lot of great things about this game.The very interesting, colourfully-designed characters are varied in playstlye, some utilizing very unique gimmicks.If you love anime, you will feel right at home, though the sprites are not as sharp or fluidly animated as you would expect in today's age.This fighter has a very complex fighting system that is pretty much on the upper echelon of skill and dedication required for mastery.However, as the spiritual successor to Guilty Gear, I was expecting something more. This game doesn't seem to play as intuitively as that game. Nor is it as fun as Guilty Gear was. Maybe because that game broke so many pre-conceived notions a standard 2D fighter.Regardless, this game is good on it's own merits, but I don't think it will ever be seen as a ""classic"" fighter.6.5/10 ""Okay"" to ""Good"""
