,Recommended,263300,17684580,"Posted: 23 August, 2015",all,xpiritflare,"Calamity Trigger is the first game in the Blazblue series, while Continuum Shift is the second (which is also on Steam). As of this review date, Chrono Phantasma is the third and latest release but is not yet on Steam, and Central Fiction will be the fourth entry to the series.Onto the review of this game, the most important thing to note is that there is no online multiplayer, which means no possibility to play online with friends or against random people. That means the only reason to buy this game is the story mode and as a cheap (while on sale) way to get into the franchise and be acquainted to the Blazblue universe and its characters.The story mode is pretty typical visual novel-esque type of gameplay. The voice options are English and Japanese with tons of voiced dialogue. Text options include: English, Chinese, Korean, French, Italian, German, Spanish and Japanese.There is no tutorial of any kind, but if you're only going to play for story mode it won't matter too much as it's fairly easy to get through it regardless of your skill.The roster size is 12.The music is exceptional."
