,Recommended,263300,19029297,"Posted: 12 November, 2015",all,Boxa,"Ok, about Blazblue. It is, probably, one of the new hits of the fighting games, and well deserved. Created by the same guys who make the Guilty Gear Series, and the Persona Arena series, both good ones, this is a game that really serves well its purposes.The commands can be a bit clunky and hard to use at first, for those that are new to the game. This is one of those games that requires a bit of you to get into it. But the idea here is to use well your 'X'(PS)/'A'(Xbox) button, since it helps to make the combos and also make the special moves. This is a game where you have to understand your character, and it is hard to pick any fighter and have some fun (you can still button smash though, that helps a lot)The problem of this game itself is the lack of any online multiplayer mode. It is understandable, since this game is really old and there is a newer game of the series here in the Steam (go look for it, Continuum Shift). But, the thing is that the story and arcade mode is good and can get yourself into the game somewhat easy, so, I only recommend it if you want to play it for the story mode. Also, if you buy it, it is nice for you to understand the mechanics of the series, or even if you play a lot with any local friend.This game gets a nice discount in sales, so I recommend that you don't buy it full price. And if you like it, go look for the Continuum Shift. It is really better."
