76561198047297216,Recommended,263300,25670694,"Posted: 24 September, 2016",all,Kokichi Oma,"Bought this a while ago to relive the Blazblue goodness, and it's everything I remember, well, except a few things. Having played Blazblue for the first time on the PSP, I was used to being able to buy the gallery in a shop, which I liked, but sadly, they did not bring the store over to the steam version, and instead linked the gallery to achievements instead. This possess a few problems, as first, steam doesn't actually have any achievements, instead, the game goes after the xbox/ps3 achievements, making it a bit hard to know what to do, second, some of the achievements are fairly hard, so casual players are locked out from that part of the gallery, and third, the game does not support online play, and since some of the achievements are tied to online play, it means it is actually impossible to complete the gallery. The game does come with its soundtrack though, and it is still the awesome game it's always been, just without the full gallery, so I'm still happy with the purchase."
