76561198002986817,Recommended,263300,28197009,"Posted: 4 December, 2016",all,Phantom Virus,"I don't know how to describe this game. At first, I didn't like it because it was unlike anything I've played before. This is litterally the first fighting game I've played through and through. The problem is that the game is really fun but its also extremely iritating with its strange save systems and the fact you can't get 100% for characters if you don't lose at least once and getting 100% is really annoying. I almost gave up the game when I started but I perservered through it. The story is good but its fractured. You never get the full picture and nothing ever makes real sense. You can put some pieces together but in the end you are always left with more questions then answers. It's hard to invest yourself when you have no clue whats going on and there are no rules to speak of. I am glad that you can play this game on keyboard and a controller isn't required. I do plan on playing its sequels but I wouldn't pay much more then I did for this one. An interesting game but not good enough to be in my favorites."
